1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,014
-Good evening.
-Good evening.

2
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:16,684
{\an8}<i>Terrace House</i> is a show about
six strangers, men and women,

3
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:18,226
{\an8}6 STRANGERS, MEN AND WOMEN,
SHARE A HOUSE

4
00:00:18,310 --> 00:00:20,938
{\an8}living together, and we observe
how they interact with each other.

5
00:00:21,021 --> 00:00:23,398
{\an8}<i>All that we've prepared is</i>
<i>a beautiful home and automobile.</i>

6
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:26,276
{\an8}-There is no script at all.
-Yes.

7
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:29,822
A lot happened last week...

8
00:00:29,905 --> 00:00:31,198
-Yes.
-Yes, indeed.

9
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:34,577
For the issue between Rikopin and Hayato,

10
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:37,120
Rikopin apologized
and practically said she likes him.

11
00:00:37,204 --> 00:00:42,793
{\an8}But maybe I gave you the idea
that I wasn't interested in you.

12
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:45,295
{\an8}I hope not.

13
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:47,172
{\an8}Because it's not true.

14
00:00:47,255 --> 00:00:49,800
{\an8}But Hayato...

15
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:54,054
He's a little scared off right now.
He says they're on hold.

16
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:58,100
Even if we did, I wouldn't be sure
whether I can take things further.

17
00:00:58,183 --> 00:01:01,478
That's true.
You couldn't even hold hands.

18
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:03,313
It'd be like a school field trip again.

19
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:05,315
-And Momochan becomes...
-Congratulations.

20
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:06,900
...a professional ballerina.

21
00:01:06,984 --> 00:01:09,903
We're so happy for her.

22
00:01:09,987 --> 00:01:13,323
{\an8}I'll be a professional dancer
starting next week.

23
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:16,660
-Wow!
-Seriously?

24
00:01:16,744 --> 00:01:19,121
-My dream came true.
-That's awesome.

25
00:01:19,204 --> 00:01:22,415
Now she can enjoy her time
at <i>Terrace House.</i>

26
00:01:22,499 --> 00:01:24,167
That's right. And now...

27
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:26,754
-The brand new...
-Misaki and Byrnes.

28
00:01:26,837 --> 00:01:30,465
A simple occurrence.
He fails to get his license.

29
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:33,593
{\an8}<i>-On Misaki's birthday.</i>
<i>-I suppose it was significant.</i>

30
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:38,556
{\an8}But later at the party,
he gives her a dress.

31
00:01:38,641 --> 00:01:41,977
<i>-That was nice.</i>
<i>-But afterward...</i>

32
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:44,604
That was great.
Let's see it again.

33
00:01:44,688 --> 00:01:45,773
They're unstoppable.

34
00:01:45,856 --> 00:01:47,775
-Can we see that part again?
-Can we?

35
00:01:47,858 --> 00:01:49,484
Can we run that scene?

36
00:01:49,567 --> 00:01:52,029
{\an8}As long as it's not Yokohama or Shonan.

37
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,906
{\an8}You don't want to go there that bad?

38
00:01:53,989 --> 00:01:55,991
{\an8}I feel like it's bad luck.

39
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:58,326
{\an8}Even if you went with a different guy?

40
00:01:58,410 --> 00:02:01,622
{\an8}"Even if you went with a different guy?"
The title for Kazumasa Oda's new single.

41
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:06,752
{\an8}-Here it comes.
-It's happening.

42
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:07,878
{\an8}"Don't stare at me..."

43
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:09,713
{\an8}Don't stare at me.

44
00:02:10,673 --> 00:02:11,840
{\an8}And then...

45
00:02:14,176 --> 00:02:16,094
{\an8}I like you, Misaki.

46
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:22,685
That carried weight.
It was the real deal.

47
00:02:22,768 --> 00:02:25,603
-It was real.
-It was that thing where it just came out.

48
00:02:25,688 --> 00:02:27,439
It just came out.

49
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:30,358
What a great moment.

50
00:02:31,068 --> 00:02:32,736
I like you.

51
00:02:35,823 --> 00:02:37,615
She's gonna file a complaint.

52
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:43,163
Oh, man! You lied, Byrnes!
It doesn't work!

53
00:02:43,246 --> 00:02:47,084
I'm sure it drove the older ladies crazy.

54
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:50,587
And he tried to lead it into a kiss.

55
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:52,798
But he was rejected.

56
00:02:57,970 --> 00:02:59,637
It's only gonna be on your forehead.

57
00:03:00,305 --> 00:03:03,851
-Just your forehead...
-Wait, wait.

58
00:03:03,934 --> 00:03:06,561
-Wait, I'm not ready...
-I'm like the weird guy.

59
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:10,899
But Misaki seemed happy.

60
00:03:10,983 --> 00:03:14,236
She was like, "Wait, you go ahead."

61
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:18,115
Isn't it a bold move
to go for a kiss so soon?

62
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:21,827
Isn't it a turn off?
Like, "Who does this guy think he is?"

63
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,829
Didn't she say something like that
at the end?

64
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:25,956
-Not at all.
-No?

65
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:27,540
I see.

66
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:30,335
I guess I am clueless.

67
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:32,880
What's wrong?

68
00:03:33,839 --> 00:03:36,133
There Triendl goes again.

69
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:38,343
I was just playing it over again
in my head.

70
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:42,097
-What?
-Byrnes and Misaki?

71
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:44,767
-It's so nice, isn't it?
-It is.

72
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:46,769
The golden days of summer.

73
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:51,523
-Summer is here, old man.
-It's summer.

74
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:10,125
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

75
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:13,921
-You're cleaning up?
-Yeah.

76
00:04:14,004 --> 00:04:16,048
Thanks. I'll help you.

77
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:27,267
I'm gonna have some cake from yesterday.

78
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:28,726
Seriously?

79
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:31,855
You can eat that now?

80
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:33,481
Totally.

81
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:40,030
-Did I seem drunk yesterday?
-Yeah.

82
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:42,740
Do you even remember what you said?

83
00:04:42,825 --> 00:04:44,117
I do.

84
00:04:45,243 --> 00:04:46,619
I see.

85
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,584
It looked really good on you though.

86
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,336
-Thanks.
-The dress.

87
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:58,173
Really good.

88
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:04,512
It...

89
00:05:05,597 --> 00:05:07,808
it just occurred to me...

90
00:05:07,891 --> 00:05:11,478
it just occurred to me
that I was really happy.

91
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:20,195
-I'm gonna go shower.
-Okay.

92
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:21,738
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

93
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:24,282
-Thanks for cleaning up, too.
-Of course.

94
00:05:25,492 --> 00:05:27,369
-See you.
-Bye.

95
00:05:32,249 --> 00:05:35,252
{\an8}SHIBUYA, TOKYO

96
00:05:37,254 --> 00:05:40,173
{\an8}What about the new member
you were talking about?

97
00:05:40,257 --> 00:05:43,093
{\an8}The new guy...

98
00:05:43,969 --> 00:05:48,140
{\an8}definitely likes one of the other girls.

99
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:50,683
{\an8}So no real potential there?

100
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:52,685
{\an8}AYAKA NISHIDA
PART-TIMER

101
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:54,021
None.

102
00:05:55,855 --> 00:06:00,485
Did you go somewhere with the 29-year-old?

103
00:06:00,568 --> 00:06:02,612
-I did.
-Seriously?

104
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:04,197
We went to Yokohama.

105
00:06:04,281 --> 00:06:06,408
Did he make any moves?

106
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:08,410
Not at all.

107
00:06:09,119 --> 00:06:11,329
If he asks you out again...

108
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:13,873
would you go?

109
00:06:13,957 --> 00:06:14,958
I would.

110
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:20,672
-But I don't think he'll ask me out again.
-Really?

111
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:24,884
So I think I'll have to do something
about that.

112
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:29,681
I think that if you ask him out,

113
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:31,308
it'd make him happy.

114
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,018
-Really?
-Yeah.

115
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:34,978
What if he says no?

116
00:06:35,062 --> 00:06:38,606
-Then...
-Like, "Sorry, I'm not feeling it."

117
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:42,527
-But things aren't awkward, right?
-Not at all.

118
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:43,820
So?

119
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:45,738
Yeah, I need to do something.

120
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:47,449
-Yeah, something.
-Something.

121
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:49,576
-I have to take action.
-Yeah.

122
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:09,179
{\an8}ARMAN BITARAF, 25 YEARS OLD,
ASPIRING FIREFIGHTER

123
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:12,140
{\an8}MISAKI TAMORI, 24 YEARS OLD,
ASPIRING ENTERTAINER, PART-TIMER

124
00:07:12,224 --> 00:07:15,227
{\an8}HAYATO TERASHIMA, 29 YEARS OLD,
CHEF-IN-TRAINING

125
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:18,396
{\an8}RIKO NAGAI, 18 YEARS OLD,
4TH YEAR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENT

126
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:21,524
{\an8}YUUKI BYRNES, 23 YEARS OLD,
HIP-HOP DANCER

127
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:25,028
{\an8}MOMOKA MITSUNAGA, 21 YEARS OLD,
BALLERINA

128
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:35,372
{\an8}ASAMI MAKI BALLET
NAKANO, TOKYO

129
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:38,458
{\an8}ASAMI MAKI BALLET

130
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:43,421
{\an8}KYOZO MITANI
ARTISTIC DIRECTOR

131
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:45,257
{\an8}-Good morning.
-Hello.

132
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:49,177
{\an8}-Congratulations on the other day.
-Thank you so much.

133
00:07:49,261 --> 00:07:51,304
-Please sit.
-Excuse me.

134
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:56,268
What did you think of the competition?

135
00:07:56,351 --> 00:08:00,480
I wanted to make the top three...

136
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:02,983
I still feel a little frustrated.

137
00:08:03,066 --> 00:08:07,529
Then your frustrations and your desire
to make the top three

138
00:08:07,612 --> 00:08:10,698
can drive you further.

139
00:08:11,158 --> 00:08:13,243
Watching you dance,

140
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:17,539
I felt that if you work hard,
you could potentially be better.

141
00:08:17,622 --> 00:08:21,459
You have presence and you have the height.

142
00:08:21,543 --> 00:08:25,505
That's what made me decide to accept you.

143
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:29,259
What you have inside of you,

144
00:08:29,342 --> 00:08:33,305
you can express to the audience
through your dance.

145
00:08:34,431 --> 00:08:37,184
So please work hard on your dancing.

146
00:08:38,268 --> 00:08:39,811
Thank you.

147
00:08:39,894 --> 00:08:42,022
Please do your best.
I'm looking forward to it.

148
00:08:42,105 --> 00:08:44,607
Thank you.
I'm looking forward to it too.

149
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:48,778
Your first class will be tomorrow,
so I'll come by to see.

150
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,324
Okay.

151
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,121
{\an8}So...

152
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:00,373
tomorrow morning...

153
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:03,710
I'll be leaving <i>Terrace House.</i>

154
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:06,796
-What? Tomorrow?
-Tomorrow?

155
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:10,383
I went to the new dance company today.

156
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:13,720
I went to talk and sign the contracts.

157
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:18,225
From now on,
everything's going to be ballet for me.

158
00:09:18,308 --> 00:09:22,354
I need to be in an environment
where I can focus on dance.

159
00:09:25,232 --> 00:09:26,816
I'll do my best.

160
00:09:28,025 --> 00:09:32,114
-I understand.
-Yeah, your dream has come true.

161
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:36,118
If that's why you're leaving,
then we support you.

162
00:09:36,201 --> 00:09:38,703
-We'll be rooting for you.
-Thank you.

163
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:43,416
I've only done ballet my entire life.

164
00:09:44,792 --> 00:09:47,254
So my time here was so much fun.

165
00:09:51,258 --> 00:09:52,759
Thank you.

166
00:09:53,468 --> 00:09:54,636
Thank you.

167
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:59,099
Over these past two months,
you only had one day off.

168
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:00,642
Thank you for spending it with me.

169
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:06,063
-That's right, I only had one day off.
-Yeah, no fair.

170
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:08,525
-No fair!
-It's not fair, Arman.

171
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:10,985
-I didn't get to go out with you.
-Yeah.

172
00:10:11,068 --> 00:10:13,655
-Thank you. It was fun.
-Thank you.

173
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:19,119
I've gone pro,
but I'm at the bottom of the ranks.

174
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:24,332
If I ever get to the middle...

175
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:28,378
I'll invite you guys to a performance.
So please come see me.

176
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:30,672
I'll go even if you're at the bottom.

177
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:33,133
Yeah, totally.

178
00:10:33,216 --> 00:10:35,177
-We want to see.
-Really?

179
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:51,943
{\an8}I'm off.

180
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:55,322
{\an8}-Good luck.
-Thank you.

181
00:10:55,405 --> 00:10:56,406
{\an8}See you.

182
00:10:57,865 --> 00:11:00,368
-I'll be going.
-Good luck.

183
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:03,246
-I'm going.
-See you.

184
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:08,084
-I'll be going.
-Thanks.

185
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:09,461
Thanks.

186
00:11:11,838 --> 00:11:13,089
I'll be going.

187
00:11:13,715 --> 00:11:15,800
-Do your best.
-Thank you.

188
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:17,469
He's carrying all my stuff.

189
00:11:19,262 --> 00:11:20,972
-See you.
-See you.

190
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:26,853
Thank you, guys.

191
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:29,063
-Work hard.
-Do your best!

192
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:38,323
{\an8}EBISU, TOKYO

193
00:11:41,326 --> 00:11:43,745
-Starting this week, I won't be alone.
-Are you going somewhere?

194
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:46,038
-I'll be living at <i>Terrace House.</i>
-What?

195
00:11:48,165 --> 00:11:50,084
-What?
-You think I'm lying, don't you?

196
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:51,794
You think I'm lying.

197
00:11:51,878 --> 00:11:54,297
Are you serious?
That's unexpected.

198
00:11:54,381 --> 00:11:57,967
-I haven't had a boyfriend for a year.
-That's true, you haven't.

199
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:01,220
-I fall for guys pretty quickly though.
-Yeah, you do.

200
00:12:02,013 --> 00:12:05,224
-You didn't have to agree.
-You do, though.

201
00:12:05,308 --> 00:12:07,852
But somehow it never works out.

202
00:12:07,935 --> 00:12:09,646
-Seriously though?
-Yeah.

203
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:12,023
Are you gonna be able to get along
with the others?

204
00:12:13,775 --> 00:12:16,528
-Because I'm a brat?
-Yeah.

205
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:19,364
Don't agree with me!

206
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:21,991
But yeah, I do fall for guys easily.

207
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:24,911
-I have a feeling it'll happen quickly.
-Oh, yeah?

208
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:27,705
Yeah, real quick.

209
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:34,921
I see. I thought she'd stick around
to enjoy her time at <i>Terrace House.</i>

210
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:38,215
But she is a professional now.
There's no need for her to stay.

211
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,217
They mentioned it in passing,
but I didn't realize

212
00:12:40,302 --> 00:12:42,679
she only had one day off
during her two months there.

213
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:44,472
What a waste!

214
00:12:44,556 --> 00:12:48,267
I mean, she spent it seeing
the comedy duo Earth with Arman.

215
00:12:48,351 --> 00:12:50,019
What a waste.

216
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:53,272
-What a waste!
-Such a waste!

217
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:56,651
And things between Byrnes and Misaki...

218
00:12:56,734 --> 00:13:00,112
I guess things are good.
I didn't need to worry.

219
00:13:00,196 --> 00:13:03,074
Very natural.
That exchange of, "Do you remember?"

220
00:13:03,157 --> 00:13:04,701
"I remember."

221
00:13:04,784 --> 00:13:08,330
And the way he said it.
It wasn't just, "I remember," but...

222
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:13,292
"I remember."
The tone shows that he meant what he said.

223
00:13:13,376 --> 00:13:14,711
Right?

224
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:17,505
Yes, he said that part seriously.

225
00:13:17,589 --> 00:13:20,592
But he then lightened it up with,
"You looked good in the dress."

226
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:24,011
{\an8}He's made us forget about Hansan.

227
00:13:24,095 --> 00:13:26,973
{\an8}-So you've recovered from the Han-loss?
-I have.

228
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:32,061
-We've got a new member.
-Yes, a new member.

229
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:35,064
She might not fit in with the group.

230
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:39,486
{\an8}Yes, she's energetic, like Hana Imai.

231
00:13:39,569 --> 00:13:42,196
{\an8}Seems like we've got a crass one.

232
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:44,198
If she falls for guys quickly, then...

233
00:13:44,281 --> 00:13:48,202
-What if she goes for Byrnes?
-It'd get complicated.

234
00:13:48,285 --> 00:13:49,996
It'd be perfect if she went for Arman.

235
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:51,581
-You want her to go for Arman?
-Yeah.

236
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,332
You're a fan of Arman.

237
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:54,959
-Yeah, you root for him.
-You like him?

238
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:57,837
Isn't he good?
He doesn't usually say anything wrong.

239
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:01,215
He doesn't,
but only because he doesn't say anything.

240
00:14:01,298 --> 00:14:05,177
{\an8}I hope we get to see her friend more too.

