00:26:39,140 --> 00:26:40,974
-Earlier...
-What?

494
00:26:41,057 --> 00:26:42,309
Earlier...

495
00:26:42,393 --> 00:26:49,275
I didn't expect Arman to ask me out
on a date on the first day.

496
00:26:49,358 --> 00:26:51,735
Is that usually how it is?

497
00:26:51,818 --> 00:26:54,946
-Like, to do something?
-To go somewhere.

498
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:57,115
I think.
I don't remember exactly.

499
00:26:57,199 --> 00:27:00,952
-Did he say where?
-I asked him where he usually goes.

500
00:27:01,036 --> 00:27:04,665
He said it depends
and to just leave it to him.

501
00:27:08,419 --> 00:27:09,836
-Really? So you said yes?
-What?

502
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:12,464
-You said yes?
-Yeah, I did.

503
00:27:13,757 --> 00:27:15,634
There's no reason for me to say no.

504
00:27:16,677 --> 00:27:17,678
Right?

505
00:27:17,761 --> 00:27:19,555
A date...

506
00:27:19,638 --> 00:27:21,307
-Is it?
-So you're going.

507
00:27:21,390 --> 00:27:22,724
Is it a date?

508
00:27:22,808 --> 00:27:27,729
But yesterday, you know how girls talk?

509
00:27:27,813 --> 00:27:30,774
They asked me who I liked
based on first impressions,

510
00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:33,527
-and I said you.
-No way.

511
00:27:33,610 --> 00:27:36,822
-But they laughed at me.
-Who did? Misaki, right?

512
00:27:36,905 --> 00:27:39,032
-She was laughing so hard.
-Misaki?

513
00:27:39,115 --> 00:27:40,784
I was like, "Why are you laughing?"

514
00:27:42,244 --> 00:27:44,079
-I see.
-Yeah.

515
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:47,208
Do you cook?

516
00:27:48,250 --> 00:27:49,668
Well...

517
00:27:49,751 --> 00:27:53,547
when I used to live with my boyfriend,

518
00:27:53,630 --> 00:27:55,090
-I did most of the cooking.
-Really?

519
00:27:55,173 --> 00:27:59,511
-But I'm sure it doesn't compare to you.
-No...

520
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:01,305
Teach me something.

521
00:28:01,388 --> 00:28:03,849
-Sure.
-Let's see...

522
00:28:03,932 --> 00:28:07,644
What would you recommend that's easy?

523
00:28:07,728 --> 00:28:09,355
I'll think about it.

524
00:28:10,689 --> 00:28:13,942
But for now, since Arman asked,
I'll go out with him.

525
00:28:15,193 --> 00:28:16,945
That's good.

526
00:28:17,028 --> 00:28:18,322
-It's good.
-It's good.

527
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:19,740
It's good.

528
00:28:21,242 --> 00:28:22,951
It's all good.

